article.headline: Yale 78, Pennsylvania 60
article.story: NEW HAVEN, Conn. (AP) -- Senior guard Edwin Draughan scored 19 points and added three assists and two steals to lead Yale to a 78-60 win over Ivy League leader Penn on Saturday night. Draughan scored seven straights points for Yale (9-12, 5-3), then assisted on an Eric Flato three-pointer during an 11-3 run that put the Bulldogs up by 12 with 10:02 left. Sophomore forward Sam Kaplan had 14 points and eight rebounds and senior guard Alex Gamboa 11 points and eight rebounds for Yale. Junior center Dominick Martin also had 11 for Yale. Sophomore forward Mark Zoller led Penn (15-8, 8-1) with 22 points, making 10 of 12 shots. He fouled out with 3:07 left, called for a moving screen. Sophomore guard Ibrahim Jaaber added 16 for Penn, which had its 11-game winning streak snapped. Draughan also defended Penn senior guard and leading scorer, Tim Begley, who was held scoreless on 0 for 6 shooting.
